title: Parkland girls soccer team rolls past Whitehall
text:
Parkland 5, Whitehall 0 â€” Rapid Recap 
Parkland girls soccer team picked up an impressive 5-0 road win over Whitehall on Wednesday night. 
Turning point : After Whitehall had some early momentum in the second half, Chelsea Hudson took a pass from Rachel Medlar and found the back of the net to extend the Trojans' lead to 2-0 with 29:26 left in the second half. Parkland took complete control of the game after that score. 
Top performer: Hudson had two goals and pair of assists as she led the Trojans, who were without injured top scorer Brooke Schutter . 
What it means : The Trojans prove they are the class of the Eastern Pennsylvania Conference with a convincing win over one of the other top teams in the conference. And they did it without their top scorer on the season.
